"""
Test 2 — Linear Motion Validation
===================================
Validates that the robot travels accurately 1 m forward then returns
1 m backward using IMU (EKF) + RPLidar fusion.

MOTOR WIRING NOTE
-----------------
  Motor direction matches the working Phase 3 logic:
      Forward:  IN1=HIGH IN2=LOW  | IN3=LOW  IN4=HIGH
      Backward: IN1=LOW  IN2=HIGH | IN3=HIGH IN4=LOW

PIN ASSIGNMENTS (BOARD numbering)
----------------------------------
  L298N:  ENA=12  IN1=13  IN2=11  IN3=16  IN4=15  ENB=35
  GY-87:  VCC=Pin1  GND=Pin6  SDA=Pin3  SCL=Pin5
  RPLIDAR USB → /dev/ttyUSB0  (auto-detected)

Motion sequence
---------------
  S1  Still  3 s    — EKF baseline / zero-velocity check
  S2  Forward       — until EKF x ≥ TARGET_M  (≈1 m)
  S3  Still  2 s    — ZUPT resets velocity drift
  S4  Backward      — until EKF x ≤ RETURN_THRESHOLD_M  (≈0 m)
  S5  Still  3 s    — final position & velocity check

Pass / Fail metrics
-------------------
  M1  EKF peak x reaches  0.85 – 1.20 m
  M2  Peak vx > 0.05 m/s             (IMU detects real motion)
  M3  LiDAR vs EKF displacement < 20 cm error
  M4  Yaw drift during straight run  < 5°
  M5  Final return |x| < 0.08 m
  M6  Final speed   < 0.01 m/s       (ZUPT working)

Safety
------
  If LiDAR detects any obstacle < OBSTACLE_STOP_MM (300 mm)
  while moving forward → motors stop immediately, test aborts.

Tuning constants (only edit these)
-----------------------------------
  PWM_SPEED        = 50    # raise if robot moves too slowly
  TARGET_M         = 1.0   # metres to drive forward
  OBSTACLE_STOP_MM = 300   # mm — emergency stop distance

Install:  pip install RPi.GPIO smbus2 rplidar-roboticia numpy
Usage:    python3 test2_linear_motion.py
          python3 test2_linear_motion.py --pwm 60
"""

import math, time, logging, threading, sys, glob, argparse
from collections import deque
import numpy as np

